<div class="widget relatedContents pictures widget-editable viziwyg-section-245 inpage-widget-158123" >
<figure class="clearfix">
<img src="http://i1.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article888428.ece/ALTERNATES/s615/Woman+swimming+at+the+beach"
width="615"
height="409"
alt=""
class=""
title=""/>
</figure>
<div class="image-credit">Getty</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="body ">
<p>If the thought of exposing your belly on ­holiday ­terrifies you, don’t panic!</p><p>Our easy but effective seven-day diet plan will help you lose up to 4lb in a week, so you look and feel great.</p><p>Bridget Benelam, senior nutrition scientist at the British Nutrition Foundation, says the secret to a flat tummy is a mix of genetic factors and a healthy eating programme.</p><p>“As we get older our ­metabolism slows and we end up storing more fat around our ­tummies – the so-called middle-aged spread,” she says.</p><p>“In addition, if you’ve inherited an ‘apple’ body shape, you may be genetically predisposed to store fat on your ­stomach and excess calories and food will unfortunately end up there.</p><p>“On top of this, our bellies are the first area affected by any digestion problems, which means salty food, a lack of fibre, constipation and stress can all leave us feeling bloated.”</p><p>But never fear. Our diet and ­exercise plan is specially designed to beat the bulge and make sure you spend your time relaxing and ­working on your tan – not worrying what you look like.</p><h2>How the diet works</h2><p>“The healthiest and most effective way to flatten your tummy is by eating a diet high in lean protein (such as chicken and fish), fruit and veg and whole grain carbs (granary bread, brown rice, etc) while boosting activity levels,” explains Bridget.</p><p>“This will not only help your body burn fat and calories, but also improve digestion and stop bloating.”</p><h2>Your seven-day meal planner (Approx 1,300 calories per day)</h2><p>
<figure class="inline-image clearfix ">
<img src="http://i3.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article888434.ece/ALTERNATES/s615/Woman+with+flat+stomach+on+the+beach"
width="615"
height="409"
alt="Woman with flat stomach on the beach"
class="captify"
title="All smiles: Your tummy will look and feel great"/>
<figcaption>All smiles: Your tummy will look and feel great</figcaption>
</figure>
<div class="image-credit">Getty</div>
 </p><h3>Day 1</h3><p>? Breakfast: Two pancakes made with 100ml semi-skimmed milk, one egg and 50g sifted wholemeal flour, cooked fat-free in a non-stick pan. Top with 2 tbsp fat-free yoghurt, 1 tsp honey and strawberries.</p><p>? Lunch: Tuna salad wrap with wholemeal pitta, 1 tsp low-fat mayo, lettuce, tomato, 170g can tuna, plus apple and glass of fruit juice of your choosing.</p><p>? Dinner: Mozzarella cod made with baked cod and basil leaves, a tomato and a 1 tsp of grated cheese, served with mixed, steamed vegetables.</p><h3>Day 2</h3><p>? Breakfast: Summer muesli made with cold semi-skimmed milk, oats, one grated apple, chopped almonds and a handful of mixed berries.</p><p>? Lunch: Prawn pasta made with wholemeal pasta, 2 tbsp tomato and basil sauce, handful prawns, handful fresh spinach and 1 tbsp grated Parmesan.</p><p>? Dinner: Small lean grilled steak, served with roasted red pepper, courgette, and butternut squash.</p><p>
<figure class="inline-image clearfix ">
<img src="http://i2.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article888427.ece/ALTERNATES/s615/Grilled+Chicken+Breast+on+Plate"
width="615"
height="410"
alt="Grilled Chicken Breast on Plate"
class="captify"
title="Grilled Chicken Breast on Plate"/>
<figcaption>Grilled Chicken Breast on Plate</figcaption>
</figure>
<div class="image-credit">Getty</div>
</p><h3>Day 3</h3><p>? Breakfast: Poached egg on wholemeal toast, no butter but with two grilled tomatoes.</p><p>? Lunch: Grilled chicken salad with mixed leaves, chopped red pepper, cucumber slices, chopped red onion, five cherry tomatoes, grilled chicken breast and 2 tbsp low-fat balsamic vinegar dressing. Two plums.</p><p>? Dinner: Vegetable chilli made using a can kidney beans, a red pepper, mushrooms, carrots, and a can of tomatoes. Serve with salad.</p><p>
<figure class="inline-image clearfix ">
<img src="http://i2.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article888420.ece/ALTERNATES/s615/Morrocan+Lemon+Chicken"
width="615"
height="410"
alt="Morrocan Lemon Chicken"
class="captify"
title="Morrocan Lemon Chicken"/>
<figcaption>Morrocan Lemon Chicken</figcaption>
</figure>
<div class="image-credit">Getty</div>
</p><h3>Day 4</h3><p>? Breakfast: Smoothie made from semi-skimmed milk, handful of strawberries and 1?2 banana.</p><p>? Lunch: Half a can of tomato and lentil soup with a granary roll and a pot of low-fat yoghurt.</p><p>? Dinner: Tuna kebabs made by threading chopped fresh tuna steaks on a skewer with nectarine and red pepper. Grill and serve with broccoli and asparagus.</p><p>
<figure class="inline-image clearfix ">
<img src="http://i4.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article888431.ece/ALTERNATES/s615/Prawn+mayonnaise+sandwich"
width="615"
height="409"
alt="Prawn mayonnaise sandwich"
class="captify"
title="Prawn mayonnaise sandwich"/>
<figcaption>Prawn mayonnaise sandwich</figcaption>
</figure>
<div class="image-credit">Getty Images</div>
</p><h3>Day 5</h3><p>? Breakfast: Two slices wholemeal toast with 2 tbsp peanut butter and an apple.</p><p>? Lunch: Sushi of three California rolls, cup of miso soup, plus two slices of fresh pineapple.</p><p>? Dinner: Moroccan lemon chicken with chicken breast baked in chopped olives, garlic, lemon slice and drizzle olive oil. Served with oven-roasted veg.</p><h3>Day 6</h3><p>? Breakfast: Bowl of porridge made from traditional oats, skimmed milk and sweetened with a little bit of honey, plus a pear.</p><p>? Lunch: Prawn sandwich made with wholemeal bread, low-fat mayonnaise, tomato and salad leaves. One pot of low-fat fruit yogurt.</p><p>? Dinner: Honey-glazed salmon with a bit of sauteed broccoli, red pepper and a small green salad with some vinaigrette.</p><p>
<figure class="inline-image clearfix portrait">
<img src="http://i2.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article888423.ece/ALTERNATES/s615b/Porridge+with+berries"
width="615"
height="768"
alt="Porridge with berries"
class="captify"
title="Porridge with berries"/>
<figcaption>Porridge with berries</figcaption>
</figure>
<div class="image-credit">Getty</div>
</p><h3>Day 7</h3><p>? Breakfast: Two toasted crumpets with a small tin of baked beans or spread with Marmite.</p><p>? Lunch: Bowl of chunky veg soup plus an open sandwich made with two slices of whole grain bread with low-fat spread and topped with tinned salmon.</p><p>? Dinner: Grilled lamb chop with steamed broccoli, peas, carrots and 1 tsp of mint sauce.</p><h3>Slimline snacks</h3><p>(choose two per day)</p><p>? Sliced apple with 1 tbsp peanut butter</p><p>? Low-fat fruit yoghurt</p><p>? Banana</p><p>
<figure class="inline-image clearfix portrait">
<img src="http://i2.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article888426.ece/ALTERNATES/s615/Sliced+Apple"
width="615"
height="409"
alt="Sliced Apple"
class="captify"
title="Sliced Apple"/>
<figcaption>Sliced Apple</figcaption>
</figure>
<div class="image-credit">Getty</div>
</p><p>? Small handful mixed nuts</p><p>? Two oatcakes with 1?2 sliced avocado</p><p>? Two chopped carrots with 2 tbsp low-fat hummus</p><h2>Beat the bloat rules</h2><p>Follows these rules between now and your hols for a flatter tum – fast</p><p>1 Take time to chew your food – it’s not just about what you eat, but also how you eat it. Smaller bits of food are easier for your stomach to break down. Eating slowly also gives your body time to feel fuller so you eat less.</p><p>2 Up your fibre intake – eat plenty of fruit, veg and whole grains as they help keep your digestive system working efficiently. Food that stays undigested in your system longer than 24 hours can release gases that bloat your tummy.</p><p>3 Take a probiotic – a supplement or daily yoghurt drink, such as Actimel or Yakult, can improve your digestion and banish bloating.</p><p>4 Ditch ready meals and fizzy drinks – the additives in processed foods and soft drinks ferment in your stomach, producing gases that well your belly.</p><p>5 Don’t eat carbs (potatoes, pasta and bread) after 6.00pm – they can leave you uncomfortably bloated. Add in extra portions of veg instead, so you don’t feel hungry.</p><p>6 Reduce salt – it encourages your body to retain water. Salt hides in everything these days, so read labels thoroughly and watch out for high sodium contents. Use herbs and spices as a substitute for salt if you want to add more flavour to your meals.</p><h2>Trimmer tummy moves</h2><p>With your holiday just around the corner, now isn’t the time to overdo things on the workout front – you don’t want to end up injured or exhausted.</p><p>Instead, aim for a brisk 20-minute walk every day to burn fat, plus the following exercises to help tone your abdominal muscles.</p><h3>The plank</h3><p>
<figure class="inline-image clearfix portrait">
<img src="http://i4.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article888461.ece/ALTERNATES/s615/Young+Woman+Doing+The+Plank"
width="615"
height="409"
alt="Young Woman Doing The Plank"
class="captify"
title="The plank"/>
<figcaption>The plank</figcaption>
</figure>
<div class="image-credit">Rex</div>
 </p><p>Lie face down then lift yourself up on to your toes and forearms, with your elbows bent at 90 degrees.</p><p>Keeping your core muscles – your stomach and bottom – tight and your legs straight, hold for 10 seconds. Repeat three times a day, gradually building to 40 seconds each.</p><h3>Bicycle crunch</h3><p>
<figure class="inline-image clearfix portrait">
<img src="http://i2.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article888425.ece/ALTERNATES/s615/Woman+doing+bicycle+crunches"
width="615"
height="409"
alt="Woman doing bicycle crunches"
class="captify"
title="Bicycle crunch"/>
<figcaption>Bicycle crunch</figcaption>
</figure>
<div class="image-credit">Nicholas Bowman</div>
</p><p>Lie down with your back pressed into the floor. Bring your hands behind your head.</p><p>Starting with your legs bent at a 45-degree angle, bring the right knee into the chest while straightening out your left leg.</p><p>At the same time, rotate your top half so your left elbow goes to  your right knee, then switch to the other side.</p><p>Repeat for one minute,three times a day.</p><h3>The boat</h3><p>
<figure class="inline-image clearfix portrait">
<img src="http://i1.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article888421.ece/ALTERNATES/s615/Woman+performing+boat+pose"
width="615"
height="409"
alt="Woman performing boat pose"
class="captify"
title="The boat"/>
<figcaption>The boat</figcaption>
</figure>
<div class="image-credit">Getty</div>
</p><p>Sit on the floor, with your knees bent and feet flat and tilt back, extending your legs so your body forms a right angle.</p><p>Pull your abs in to balance. Extend your arms at shoulder height past your knees. Hold for five slow breaths and return to your starting position.</p><p>Repeat five times a day.</p><h2>Look slimmer in your holiday snaps</h2><p>1 Never stand straight on to the camera. Turn your hips to the side and twist your upper body back to the photographer to create a waist and narrow your widest parts.</p><p>2 Think about what you’re wearing. If you’ve been sunbathing in a skimpy bikini pull a kaftan or a sarong over unsightly lumps and bumps before the camera comes out.</p><p>3 Stand or sit tall and don’t hunch. Slouching will not only make you appear shorter but it will also create rolls on your stomach, so pull your tummy in, and your shoulders back and down.</p><p>4 Are you worried about your upper arms? Then don’t stand with them pressed against your body but rest your hands on your hips and ensure there is a gap between your arms and your torso.</p><p>5 To prevent the dreaded double chin, lift yours up and push it out before looking up to the camera. Always look up to the camera, never down, to slim your face.</p><p>6 A good posture can take inches off your frame so lengthen your spine and hold your head high – imagine there’s a string pulling you up through the crown of your head.</p><p>7 Never cross you legs at the thighs, it will only highlight cellulite. Instead, have both feet flat on the ground or cross at the ankle.</p><p>8 Think happy thoughts and work on a natural smile – your face is the first thing anyone looks at.</p><p>9 Use props. Your oversized bag is the perfect thing to hide a big tummy and you can always disguise thighs beneath a bright beach towel.</p><p>10 When photographed with other people make sure you are slightly further back than the others. The bodies at the front will always appear bigger as they are closer to the lens.</p>
</div>
